## How to Use This Repo Today

Until Phase 1 lands, this repository is best read as a project blueprint:

1. Start with this README for the product idea.
2. Read [`docs/ROADMAP.md`](./docs/ROADMAP.md) to understand the delivery sequence.
3. Read [`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`](./docs/ARCHITECTURE.md) to understand the planned system.
4. Read [`docs/DECISIONS_LOG.md`](./docs/DECISIONS_LOG.md) to see why key choices were made.

Once the backend exists, this section will be replaced with real setup and run commands.

## Project Principles

- Build in small phases and keep each phase working before moving on.
- Prefer clear, explainable code over clever abstractions.
- Keep every service containerized.
- Avoid committing secrets.
- Use local AI as infrastructure, not as an external paid dependency.
- Keep the project useful for learning, portfolio review, and eventual personal use.

